snippet: Contracts to buy previously owned homes reached an eight-month high in May, the latest indication that housing was pulling out of a recent soft patch.
abstract: National Association of Realtors says that contracts to buy previously owned homes rose 6.1 percent to reach eight-month high in May, latest indication that housing is pulling out of a recent soft patch.
lead_paragraph: Contracts to buy previously owned homes reached an eight-month high in May, the latest indication that housing was pulling out of a recent soft patch.

headline.main: Pending Home Sales Hit 8-Month High in May
headline.print_headline: Pending Homes Sales Hit an 8-Month High in May
